Date:  0/0/1967
Source:  Animals of NZ, The
Author:  NATUSCH
Vol / Page:  226
Edition:
Quote:  The common bully (<i>Gobiomorphus</i> sp(p)) is plentiful at river mouths, and occurs also in some upland lakes like Te Anau and Alexandria. The giant bully,<i> G. gobioides,</i> grows up to nine inches long - three inches longer than the biggest common bully - and is most often met with in lowland lake, swamps and spring-fed creeks.
Notes:

